<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-242-053 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 351 334</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  Jan 16 1991 n150 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business andamp; Computer Publications(England) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Excel 3.0 moves across multiple platforms. (Microsoft Corp.)andO;(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Excel 3.0 (Spreadsheet software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSpreadsheetsEnhancementsGraphical User Interface.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Microsoft put greater distance between itself and Lotus last week with thelatest version of its graphical user interface Excel 3.0,andM;The major changes in the product, which is available for Windows, OS/2 andMacintosh users, includes a toolbar, 3D rotating charts, outlining facilitiesand built-in Q+E,andM;Excel product manager, Andrew Lees, believes that users are now converted tothe use of graphics-based programs, which gives the company an advantage overcompetitor Lotus, which still has to release a Windows version of itsspreadsheet 1-2-3.andM;According to Lees, Microsoft examined the way in which spreadsheet usersworked and found that 20 per cent of the functionality was used most of thetime.andP;  The changes are intended to maximise this functionality.andM;A toolbar down the side of the worksheet gives users point and check accessto new features, such as the Autosum function which automatically creates thesum formula.andP;  This is in response to Microsoft's discovery that sum worktakes 70 per cent of users' time.andM;The Q+E utility has been absorbed into the main package allowing users toretrieve information elsewhere on the network without leaving Excel.andM;Analysis features have been supplemented with the inclusion of a Solverfacility.andP;  This increases the speed and ease with which users can estimatechanges in their tables while assigning constraints on particular variables.andM;Excel 3.0 also provides goal-seeking facilities through charts as well asworksheets.andP;  An outlining facility allows users to zoom-in on differentlevels of detail within a large spreadsheet.andM;Work on the graphics capabilities of the product means that users can nowrotate four chart types in three dimensions.andM;Toolbar icons also allow you to draw circles and ellipses straight on to theworksheet rather than import them from another application.andM;Prices for the package are [british pounds] 395 for Windows and OS/2 whilethe Macintosh version costs [british pounds] 345.andP;  Upgrades for existing 2.1versions cost [british pounds] 75.andM;The Windows version has already started shipping while the OS/2 and Macintoshversions are expected to follow shortly.andO;</TEXT></DOC>